            }, {
              "attributes" : {
                "dxpStyle" : { },
                "markupText" : "<div class=\"govuk-width-container\">     <main class=\"govuk-main-wrapper\" id=\"main-content\" role=\"main\">         <h1 class=\"govuk-heading-xl\">Register a private rented sector exemption</h1>         <p class=\"govuk-body\">The <abbr title=\"Minimum Energy Efficiency Standard\" class=\"govuk-!-font-weight-bold\">MEES</abbr> Regulations 2015 set a minimum energy efficiency standard for private rented properties.</p>         <h2 class=\"govuk-heading-l\">When you need an EPC or an exemption</h2>         <p class=\"govuk-body\">To rent a property out, it must have an energy performance certificate (EPC) rating of <strong>Band E or higher</strong>, or have a valid exemption.</p>         <div class=\"govuk-inset-text\">             <p class=\"govuk-body\">Use this service to register an exemption for a property if:</p>             <ul class=\"govuk-list govuk-list--bullet\">                 <li>you are letting or are planning to let your property</li>                 <li>the energy performance certificate (EPC) rating is Band <strong>F</strong> or <strong>G</strong></li>                 <li>you are unable to raise the EPC rating to Band <strong>E</strong> or above</li>             </ul>         </div>         <p class=\"govuk-body\">You can also use this service to manage any existing exemptions that your property has.</p>         <h2 class=\"govuk-heading-l\">Before you start</h2>         <p class=\"govuk-body\">You should:</p>         <ul class=\"govuk-list govuk-list--bullet\">             <li><a href=\"https://draft-origin.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/publications/private-rented-sector-exemptions-prse-landlord-guidance?token=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiIzZWMwNmNmMy04N2FhLTQ3NzItOTc4Zi1kYTg4ZjM3OWEyMTIiLCJjb250ZW50X2lkIjoiOGM4NWU3Y2MtNWM5YS00ZmRkLWE0ZmUtMDJkMjkyNWUyZDk3IiwiaWF0IjoxNzYxODE2MTIyLCJleHAiOjE3NjQ0OTQ1MjJ9.6jgo5wbdqKqbGnt9f4w2klX0ypKY9gRX0iIQ1yDtNS4\" class=\"govuk-link\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\">read our guidance on exemptions (opens in new tab)</a></li>             <li>gather the evidence you need</li>             <li>seek legal advice, if you are unsure which exemptions apply to your property</li>         </ul>         <div class=\"govuk-warning-text\" role=\"region\" aria-labelledby=\"warning-heading\"> <span class=\"govuk-warning-text__icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\">!</span> <strong id=\"warning-heading\" class=\"govuk-warning-text__text\"> <span class=\"govuk-warning-text__assistive\">Warning</span> You can be fined up to £5,000 if you provide false or misleading information </strong> </div>         <p class=\"govuk-body\">When you register an exemption, it applies immediately. You may be contacted by your local authority to provide more evidence.</p>         <p class=\"govuk-body\">If you are registering an exemption as an agent on behalf of a landlord, you or the landlord may be contacted to provide more evidence.</p>"
              },
              "definition" : "uxgovuk:govMarkupText",
              "id" : "cf414105-a3fc-48e9-a6b7-1ed801d0924c",
              "type" : "component"
            }, {
